  "prompt": "In which attempt is NET/SET exam cleared approximately?",
  "response": "The success rate in clearing the NET (National Eligibility Test) or SET (State Eligibility Test) exams can vary widely among candidates. Many candidates may clear the exam on their first attempt, while others may take multiple attempts.\n\n1. **First Attempt**: Some candidates are well-prepared and clear it in their first attempt.\n2. **Multiple Attempts**: It's common for candidates to take more than one attempt. Many candidates clear it within 2 to 3 attempts, while others may take longer, depending on their study habits, understanding of the syllabus, and exam strategies.\n\nUltimately, the number of attempts required to clear the NET/SET exams depends on individual preparation levels, familiarity with the subject matter, and exam techniques. It's essential to prepare thoroughly and understand the exam pattern and syllabus to increase the chances of success.",
